"They are trying to deceive God
and the believers."

513
01:16:27,800 --> 01:16:34,240
" But they deceive none but
themselves and do not realize it."

514
01:16:34,400 --> 01:16:40,640
" Their hearts are sick and
God lets their disease getting worse" -

515
01:16:40,800 --> 01:16:47,080
" and a painful punishment awaits them
for their constant lies."

516
01:16:47,240 --> 01:16:52,800
"When they are urged not to sow discord
on Earth, they answer."

517
01:16:52,960 --> 01:16:56,840
"We just want to improve and make amends."

518
01:16:57,000 --> 01:17:01,600
"No, it is they who create discord
and spreads depravation."

519
01:17:01,760 --> 01:17:05,200
"But they do not realize."

520
01:17:11,360 --> 01:17:15,280
It was excellent, Wadjda.
God bless you.

521
01:17:21,320 --> 01:17:23,920
Will you say your prayer next to us?

522
01:17:24,080 --> 01:17:28,120
- Congratulations.
- The winner is yet to be declared.

523
01:17:28,280 --> 01:17:32,280
You won. You're their favorite.
Their votes will be unanimous.

524
01:17:32,440 --> 01:17:38,720
Wadjda, come up!
We kept a place for you in the front row.

525
01:17:38,880 --> 01:17:40,400
Coward.

526
01:17:43,720 --> 01:17:46,400
Fall in line.

527
01:17:47,000 --> 01:17:52,960
Stand closer together.
Leave no room for the devil.

528
01:17:53,120 --> 01:17:56,400
God is great.

529
01:18:15,760 --> 01:18:19,360
God hears the prayer of thanks.

530
01:18:33,400 --> 01:18:37,320
Quiet, girls. Silence!

531
01:18:40,400 --> 01:18:44,200
Finalists in the competition.

532
01:18:44,360 --> 01:18:49,400
Noura Saleh, Salma Abdul Aziz
and Wadjda Al Saffan.

533
01:18:49,560 --> 01:18:54,360
And now... the third prize goes to...

534
01:18:54,560 --> 01:18:57,360
Salma Abdul Aziz.

535
01:18:58,360 --> 01:19:00,320
Congratulations.

536
01:19:01,280 --> 01:19:04,840
Winner of the second prize is....

537
01:19:06,920 --> 01:19:09,960
Noura Saleh.

538
01:19:10,120 --> 01:19:12,480
Congratulations, Noura.

539
01:19:16,320 --> 01:19:18,680
Wadjda, the first prize goes to you.

540
01:19:18,840 --> 01:19:23,360
You won thanks to your dedication and the
fact that you have been so diligent.

541
01:19:23,520 --> 01:19:27,520
I hope everyone here
today learn from your example.

542
01:19:27,680 --> 01:19:30,080
Congratulations.

543
01:19:34,160 --> 01:19:38,720
And what do you intend to use
prize money for?

544
01:19:38,880 --> 01:19:43,360
I want to buy a bike at the store
down the street.

545
01:19:43,520 --> 01:19:45,480
What did you say?

546
01:19:45,640 --> 01:19:52,600
I want to buy a bike, but without training
wheels because I can ride a bike.

547
01:20:03,360 --> 01:20:10,000
Wouldn't it be better to donate the money
for our brothers in Palestine?

548
01:20:13,240 --> 01:20:15,720
A bike is not for girls.

549
01:20:15,880 --> 01:20:20,920
Especially not for the benefit of girls
who are afraid of their honor.

550
01:20:21,560 --> 01:20:26,160
I'm sure your family will not allow it.

551
01:20:26,320 --> 01:20:32,280
The money will be donated in your name and
May God reward you for the good work.

552
01:20:32,440 --> 01:20:36,240
Now go back to your place.

553
01:20:40,120 --> 01:20:44,000
That's all girls. You can go now.

554
01:20:45,840 --> 01:20:49,160
So nothing's changed after all.

555
01:20:49,320 --> 01:20:52,640
Do you think your behaviour
will go unnoticed?

556
01:20:52,800 --> 01:20:58,800
Your silly attitude
will haunt you forever.

557
01:21:01,040 --> 01:21:04,960
You mean like your "fancy" thief?

558
01:21:31,440 --> 01:21:35,040
Didn't you win? Where is the money?

559
01:21:35,200 --> 01:21:38,080
In Palestine.

560
01:21:57,040 --> 01:22:03,400
- I'll give you my bike.
- How can race with one bike?

561
01:22:05,160 --> 01:22:07,320
Wadjda....

562
01:22:08,880 --> 01:22:15,720
You know I want to marry you
when we grow up, right?

563
01:22:47,000 --> 01:22:50,840
So. You're finally home.

564
01:22:51,000 --> 01:22:57,760
- What's with the new haircut?
- Your mother does not answer my calls.

565
01:22:57,920 --> 01:23:00,960
Can I see?

566
01:23:01,120 --> 01:23:07,400
You won? I don't think that's true.
You are my little darling.

567
01:23:08,800 --> 01:23:12,280
Why are you crying? You won after all.

568
01:23:13,240 --> 01:23:16,440
Wait a second.
- Hello?

569
01:23:17,680 --> 01:23:20,320
Are you ready?

570
01:23:29,200 --> 01:23:33,680
I'm so proud of you,
my little heroine.

571
01:23:33,840 --> 01:23:37,240
I have tried to call your mom all day.

572
01:23:37,400 --> 01:23:41,120
When she comes home,
tell her I love her.

573
01:23:58,040 --> 01:24:01,920
Hello? Hello, Aunt Leila.

574
01:24:02,080 --> 01:24:05,040
No, I don't know where she is.

575
01:24:07,320 --> 01:24:11,160
Yes, she is usually home by this time.

576
01:24:12,200 --> 01:24:14,920
Okay, I'll tell her.

577
01:24:15,080 --> 01:24:17,120
Goodbye.

578
01:25:28,360 --> 01:25:31,400
Congratulations, I heard the news.

579
01:25:31,560 --> 01:25:36,160
They said you won.
I couldn't believe it.

580
01:25:36,320 --> 01:25:41,160
When you go after something,
no one can stop you.

581
01:25:43,280 --> 01:25:50,120
- I did not get the money.
- Why did you say you wanted to buy the bike?

582
01:25:50,280 --> 01:25:55,200
Anyway, you don't need them or their money.

583
01:26:01,120 --> 01:26:07,920
What happened at grandma's? I thought
the marriage was not until next month?

584
01:26:08,360 --> 01:26:11,800
It was not your uncle's wedding.

585
01:26:22,000 --> 01:26:28,560
It's okay. He has made his decision.
It's just you and me now.

586
01:26:45,040 --> 01:26:50,840
Let's buy the red dress
and go fetch Dad.

587
01:26:51,000 --> 01:26:57,680
The dress is no longer needed.
Besides, I already spent the money.

588
01:27:18,040 --> 01:27:20,920
I hope it is right.

589
01:27:21,080 --> 01:27:25,800
The shopkeeper had held it for
a brave little girl.

590
01:27:25,960 --> 01:27:28,960
I want you to be the happiest person.

591
01:27:29,120 --> 01:27:32,960
You're all I have left in this world.

592
01:28:54,760 --> 01:28:56,400
- Abdalla.
- Goal!

593
01:29:26,040 --> 01:29:29,400
Catch me if you can.
